I don&#x27;t like repeating function calls, if logic calls for complex conditions (which I don&#x27;t think the example does) I find it better to express them in new booleans before the if, keeping the logic contained there, and call them on a:<p><pre><code>  bool shouldDoSomethingElse = a && b;

  if(a) doSomething();

  if(shouldDoSomethingElse) doSomethingElse();
</code></pre>
kind of thing.
